  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We extend the Implicit Regularization (IR) technique, in which the divergent content of an amplitude is displayed in terms of basic divergent integrals in the loop momenta, to massless infrared safe theories at arbitrary loop order . It turns out that, order by order in perturbation theory, the infrared cutoff at the level of propagators cancels out due to a subtle interplay between divergent and finite parts of the amplitude. This mechanism gives as a byproduct the renormalization group scale within IR. We illustrate the mechanism with the $\lambda^3_6$ theory.</subfield>
  </datafield>
